# Charmingly Awkward

| rev2      =
| rev2Score =
}}
Charmingly Awkward is the first studio album by the rock band Street To Nowhere. It was independently released in 2005, and officially released in 2006 through Capitol Records.
Track listing
#"Screamin" - 3:12
#"Boxcars Boxcars Boxcars"  – 4:30
#"Georgia, Can You Hear Me?"  – 5:04
#"Miss Rolling Eyes" - 4:49
#"Waste My Life For You" - 2:23
#"Dead Cliché" - 3:17
#"Tipsy"  – 4:49
#"The Sun" - 3:43
#"They're Not Like Us"  – 3:10
#"Leave the Cameras On" - 2:42
#"You Can't Go To Sleep" - 5:59
Information
# Featured various members of Bay Area bands on the end of "Tipsy".
# Recorded in 10 different places, including apartments, basements, living rooms, and even a cabin.
# Dave celebrated three birthdays in the time it took from the first tracks to be laid down until the release.
# Recorded on a budget gathered from local shows and sales of t-shirts and demos.
# Dave Smallen created the cover art.
